review:
Spectacular game! Had some performance issues but apart from that the game is stuning:

- Good Graphics;
- Appealing UI;
- Accurate & immersive scennery;
- Lore is interesting & captivating;
- Gameplay is smooth and easy to understand;

9/10, was left wishing for at least a 2nd mission after the 1st one or else I'd give It a 10 :)

Another wonderful game from one of my favorite devs! Who doesn't love bunnies? Balls of hopping fluff and happiness. As the dev accustomed us, there are 16 levels with jaw-dropping artworks and relaxing music. In each level the player has to find half a hundred bunnies, half a hundred carrots. Some are well hidden even for the HO expert! With a bit of luck and an eagle eye, you can achieve them all!

PROS:
- Wonderful artwork;
- Nice, relaxing music;
- Easy to difficult modes;
- Hundreds of bunnies and carrots to collect;
- Easy to obtain achievements.

NEUTRE:
- Next time, I want squirrels and acorns!!!

CONS:
- It has become a traditional plane HO game. It definitely needs some seasoning. I recommend the dev to include a hidden room / location or to make a clickable interactive environment. Something like that. 
- Nothing else.

In conclusion, play it! A game worth the experts and the initiates of Hidden Object games!

